         <abstract>
            <p>The "polar" method of Box and Muller uses two independent uniform variates in order to generate two independent normal variates. It can be adapted so that two variates from Student's t-distribution with parameter Î½ are generated, though the two variates are now not independent. An algorithm based on the polar method is exact, inexpensive, and valid for all &lt;latex&gt;$\nu &gt; 0$&lt;/latex&gt;.</p>
          </abstract>
